commit_list.message:
Fix Issue #21 - Configuration management

This implements the configuration setup and save mechanism, for example,
executing the command `$ checklister setup` gives you this kind of
configuration wizard:

![](https://www.dropbox.com/s/8lu6kpzijbufews/checklister__bash__Solarized_Dark_xterm-256color__9741_2015-09-15_06-58-04.png?dl=1)

You can also read the currently saved services by using this command `$
checklister settings` after picking the services you are interested in,
it will display the currently saved configuration (by default, it's in a
file `~/.checklister.yml`

Once this branch is ready to squash and merge, we should have an easy
way to access user defined settings in our gem (especially when
interacting with gitlab remote service...))
